snippet.textDisplay: My heart goes out for Vanessa. I would have loved to hear Kobe's parents speak on behalf of their son. They looked sad. They lost their son and granddaughter. For the world to honor their son with such beautiful words had to make them feel happy.  I  hope Kobe and his parents last words to each other were uplifting words. To Kobe's parents,  you took time to raise a wonderful person. Everyone can see that he loved his wife and children and that type of person have to have good parents. Children have conflicts with their parents but the love is still there. God  knows how you feel. Stay close  to God. You have my condolences. You have the great pleasure of knowing your son wrote a short film about his dad playing basketball and how he admired and was proud of his dad. The movie is part of his legacy and your's. Have comfort in knowing Vanessa is a good mother and she will raise your grandchildren to be good people. So congratulations to you for having raised a wonderful son.
